# Tor configuration for Nimble Node.
#
# The tor container runs as an independent sidecar on the "lan" bridge network.
# LND (in the lit container) reaches it by service name over the internal
# network: SOCKS on tor:9050 and the control port on tor:9051. LND creates and
# manages its own v3 onion service through the control port and forwards it to
# LND's p2p listener (see lnd.tor.targetipaddress in entrypoint.sh).
#
# The ports bind to 0.0.0.0 so they are reachable from the lit container, but
# they are NOT published to the host, so they stay on the internal docker
# network only. Access is restricted to the docker subnet + loopback, and the
# control port additionally requires the control cookie (the standard method),
# shared with lit through the tor-data volume.

SocksPort 0.0.0.0:9050
SocksPolicy accept 172.28.0.0/16
SocksPolicy accept 127.0.0.0/8
SocksPolicy reject *

ControlPort 0.0.0.0:9051
CookieAuthentication 1
CookieAuthFileGroupReadable 1

DataDirectory /var/lib/tor
Log notice stdout
